    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-53-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "For the leader; on mahalath.A maskil of David."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-53-1-commentary-1",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "Cf. Ps. 14.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "ps",
        "chapter": 53,
        "verse": 1
      },
      "verse_start": 1,
      "verse_end": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-53-1-commentary-2",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "Meaning of Heb. unknown.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "ps",
        "chapter": 53,
        "verse": 1
      },
      "verse_start": 1,
      "verse_end": 1
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-53-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "The benighted man thinks, “God does not care.” Man’s wrongdoing is corrupt and loathsome; no one does good."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-53-2-commentary-3",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "Lit. “There is no God”; cf. Ps. 10.4.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "ps",
        "chapter": 53,
        "verse": 2
      },
      "verse_start": 2,
      "verse_end": 2
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-53-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "God looks down from heaven on mankind to find a man of understanding, a man mindful of God."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-53-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "Everyone is dross, altogether foul; there is none who does good, not even one."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-53-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "Are they so witless, those evildoers, who devour my people as they devour food, and do not invoke God?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-53-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "There they will be seized with fright —never was there such a fright— for God has scattered the bones of your besiegers; you have put them to shame, for God has rejected them."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-53-6-commentary-4",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "Meaning of Heb. uncertain.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "ps",
        "chapter": 53,
        "verse": 6
      },
      "verse_start": 6,
      "verse_end": 6
    },
    {
      "block_id": "jsb-ps-53-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "O that the deliverance of Israel might come from Zion! When God restores the fortunes of His people, Jacob will exult, Israel will rejoice."
    }
  ]
}